<br>
Personally, I just ignore the OOC names unless they really strike a nerve with me.  I'm sorry, perhaps I'll be branded a petty petitioner...but rude names like &quot;Stillborn&quot;, &quot;Castration&quot;, and &quot;Lookitsanegro&quot; (yes, I DID see these people), will get a petition from me.  However, I just let Rogue names with &quot;Stab&quot;, Warrior and Ranger FIRST names with &quot;blade&quot;, and monk names with every sort of Bruce Lee or DragonballZ reference, pass on by.  <br>
<br>
Just last night, there were people named &quot;thiserversux&quot;, &quot;paineelian&quot;, and &quot;yowhatsup&quot; running around in Odus.  Oh well...what can you do?<br>
<br>
By the way, I play a pretty mean game of Quake/Unreal Tournament.  In fact, my old monicker, Ronin47, should still be on NGstats.  I miss my old days of playing Quake II with the Loki's Minions CTF, Rocket Arena, and Weapons of War Mods.  Heck, I even named myself &quot;Johnny Bravo&quot; back then...<br>
<br>
Nevertheless, none of the characters I've created in Everquest violate the existing naming rules.  I guess I'm just one of those who plays FPS games and still creates decent roleplay type names.  Perhaps I'm just a freak of nature.  Oh wait, I'm a half elf bard....never mind... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
