<br>
I don't care what peoples toons names are here. That wasn't my point. I am just sick of the dumb ass class/race based names that seem to all be variations on 10 words.<br>
<br>
As I also already said, I used those games off the top of my head, not cause I don't like them, but becuase I dunno where some of these people come from, since it is most likely not from old school RPGs.<br>
<br>
With LotR out now and some threads on the board about it, how seriously would people read a book like that or take the movie if the characters were all named goofy class names?<br>
<br>
As Sleil pointed out, this is opinion. Nothing more. Some people share it and some don't. No biggie. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#B8C0C7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukneelingmonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KneelingMonk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.home.net/gcarnegie/yinyang.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Proud Owner of Baby Bushido</span><br>  Posts: 806<br> <font color=#122950>(12/23/01 4:55:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2184.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kneelingmonk.homestead.com/files/skullfire.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please go back to Doom/Quake/Unreal Tournament</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Being a PURE roleplaying game, there were never ever any instances of &quot;non-roleplaying&quot; names in D&amp;D? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
